Here’s to reigniting hope when it was lost,
Here’s to restoring faith when believing seemed impossible, 
Here’s to being the light where there was darkness.

Dear Doctor, here’s to you..

As we confine to deliver on our commitment to provide you with the best care in the world, it is the trust of many key leaders and dignitaries that we'll continue to build Apollo to be the most loved and trusted healthcare institution in the world.

Reaching the mountain peaks even after Knee Replacement Surgery.

Hear the inspiring story of a 68-year-old man who, despite having knee replacement surgery, decided to fulfil his lifelong desire of going on a trek. Retired SBI employee Mr. Anil Sharma beat the odds and trekked to Mount Everest's base camp after having knee replacement surgery at Apollo Hospitals under the supervision of Dr. Mehta. Our admiration for you extends from the time you struggled to walk 100-200 metres to the time you conquered Mount Everest. We have more faith in doctors and the healthcare community as a whole because to Mr. Sharma's narrative.

#ApolloHospitals #Trekking

In celebration of Azadi Ka Amrit Mahotsav and to commemorate 75 years of independence, members of Team Apollo from across the country paid tribute to our nation. Here's a glimpse of how we celebrated the spirit of independence.

#IndependenceDay #75thIndependence #ApolloHospitals #India #azadikaamritmahotsav #harghartiranga #AzadIndia

We appreciate Dr. Ali Ishtiaq for sharing Afsheen Gul’s story. Do watch his take on the medical miracle, made possible by Dr. Rajagopalan Krishnan of Indraprastha Apollo Hospitals.

On June 5, 2022, eight courageous cancer survivors embarked on an enthralling adventure - a five-day trek to summit a peak 11,380 ft high. Determined to challenge the norm and send across a message that #WinningOverCancer is not just winning over the disease but living life to the fullest. Here is a glimpse of what ensued and how these courageous eight summited yet another peak to become beacons of hope and proved that life is greater than cancer.

This Doctors’ Day let’s celebrate those who are our light in the darkest of nights.

Apollo Hospitals pays tribute to the #Doctors whose days include working through endless nights. Ensuring that there is always someone you can turn to when health takes a turn for the worst.

This Doctors’ Day, Apollo celebrates those who give up the comfort of their beds to be at our bedsides.

Apollo celebrates those who give us their nights, night after night.

#ApolloHospitals  #DoctorsDay #NationalDoctorsDay #DoctorsDay2022

Watch how an 8-year-old braveheart from Bihar, Anshika Kumari battled Liver problems due to Wilson's disease and came out victorious days later!

She received a live donor liver transplant from her mother and made a successful recovery without any complications with the help and guidance of our team of expert doctors and staff at the Apollo Hospitals, Delhi.

#ApolloHospitals #WilsonsDisease #Liver

Watch the insights on "What should be the first step in treating a burn?" by Dr. K.V. Lokesh, consultant emergency medicine, Apollo Hospitals.

Some steps for treating burns:
1. Cool the burn.
2. Remove rings or other tight items from the burned area.
3. Don't break blisters.
4. Apply lotion.
5. Bandage the burn.
6. If needed, take a nonprescription pain reliever, such as ibuprofen (Advil, Motrin IB, others), naproxen sodium (Aleve) or acetaminophen (Tylenol, others).

#ApolloHospitals #FirstAid #Emergencies

Did you know that yoga asanas can help you maintain your health and recover from a variety of illnesses?

There are many different yoga practices that can be tailored to your body's demands and temperament. Hatha yoga, Vinyasa yoga, Bikram yoga, Restorative yoga, and Ashtanga yoga are among them. Exploring various yoga techniques and selecting the one that best suits your needs might have a big impact on your recovery time.

#ApolloHospitals #InternationalYogaDay

As part of our mission to bring international healthcare standards within everyone’s reach, Apollo Hospitals is collaborating with Imperial Hospital Limited in Bangladesh, bringing patient-focused medical care to over 166 million people.
 
With this partnership, we’re contributing to the healthcare ecosystem, through clinical excellence and a healing environment that inspires belief amongst patients. 

#WinningOverCancer #ApolloImperialHospitals #Bangladesh #India

On this occasion of International Nurses Day, Apollo Cancer Centres celebrates the ones who dedicate their lives to serving others. We would not be who we are today if it were not for you.

Wishing all our angels a Happy International Nurses Day.

May all the care and kindness you give to others come back to warm your hearts.

#InternationalNursesDay #WinningOverCancer #ApolloCancerCentres
